{
  "stem": "12491.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "They wouldn't let you come up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And this took for three-- this took time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "This took three days.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "After three days, I was done with the penalty.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "This was one of the horrible situations, because dozens and dozens of people fell in, never to show up.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This I will have to backtrack, because really I was not present.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I did not see him there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm going with my story, and then I will backtrack to that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "About a month later, which would be probably towards the end of September, 1944, the Germans supposedly got an order to evacuate the camp and move all the prisoners, the Jews, to other camps.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But before they do that, they were supposed to destroy any evidence of their killing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The evidence of the killing was in a ravine, all-- all within the camp-- within camp itself, where they shot many people, who fell into the ravine.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They just put dirt and some disinfectant over them, and shot the next group, and they were laying right on top of the other.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And eventually, that thing was buried with dirt, and it was a mass grave.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But when the order came to evacuate, and destroy the evidence of their action, they decided to un-dig the people.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we had to work in un-digging these corpses, and they were burning the corpses.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I don't wish to refer to the but this is all shown there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In the process, they were examining-- some Jews were assigned to do that-- examining people's teeth, and pull gold teeth, and bury the-- bury the corpses otherwise.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Whether they finished the job totally or not, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I worked there for two or three days, and I was free.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
